HEADWORD: Waning
<hw>Wan"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or process of
waning, or decreasing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This earthly moon, the Church, hath fulls and <qex>wanings</qex>,
and sometimes her eclipses.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wanion</ent>⟦br⟧
